  "text": "Although patients with postoperative PSA recurrences often undergo ADT before there is any evidence of metastatic disease, the benefit of this approach is uncertain. Some retrospective studies do not show differences in the time to clinical metastases compared to delayed ADT and do not allow any definitive conclusion on the use of early ADT [CITATION_1] . In any case, patients without evidence of metastatic disease should not be offered any of the new antiandrogen treatments outside a clinical trial.",
